( 1. Executive Summary & Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter analyses fictitious ad-click traffic to identify events that look) Tj
T*
(more like automated bot activity than legitimate user behaviour. The business) Tj
T*
(challenge is a familiar one for advertising platforms: invalid clicks can) Tj
T*
(inflate campaign metrics, distort billing, reduce trust in performance) Tj
T*
(reporting, and consume operational time that should be spent on genuine) Tj
T*
(customer outcomes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This run read data/bot-hunter-dataset.tsv and analysed 149,239 click) Tj
T*
(events. Each row contains an event identifier, timestamp, region, browser,) Tj
T*
(operating system, and click URL. The URL query string carries behaviour signals) Tj
T*
(such as clicked domain \(d\), search query \(q\), time to click \(ttc\), and) Tj
T*
(country-like context \(ct\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter selected 3,731 events, or 2.50% of the batch, as) Tj
T*
(likely bot traffic for review. This is a meaningful operational finding: even a) Tj
T*
(small invalid-click rate can affect revenue assurance, customer confidence,) Tj
T*
(campaign optimisation, and the credibility of downstream reporting.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This report should be read as evidence for review, not as proof of fraud for) Tj
T*
(every individual event. The dataset does not include ground-truth labels, so) Tj
T*
(the system cannot claim measured precision, measured recall, or a calibrated) Tj
T*
(fraud probability. The submitted output is submission.tsv. It keeps the) Tj
T*
(required binary is_bot decision and adds operational_tier so the same) Tj
T*
(prediction can be used carefully in business workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 2. Methodology & Rationale) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter uses two classifiers because the risk has two different shapes. A) Tj
T*
(rules classifier catches patterns that are easy to explain and audit, such as) Tj
T*
(repeated query/domain pairs, mechanical timing, and dense bursts. The) Tj
T*
(Extended Isolation Forest model catches unusual combinations across engineered features) Tj
T*
(that) Tj
T*
(fixed rules may miss.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This combined design was chosen over a simpler single-rule approach because a) Tj
T*
(single rule is too brittle for adversarial traffic. For example, a bot can) Tj
T*
(avoid one obvious threshold while still leaving a broader statistical footprint) Tj
T*
(across timing, repeated terms, clicked domains, and device-like context. The) Tj
T*
