( 6. Probability Perspective & Risk Assessment) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current operational confidence estimate is 74.49%. This is not) Tj
T*
(measured precision because the dataset has no ground-truth labels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Confidence is higher when independent signals agree: for example, when a) Tj
T*
(strong repeated query/domain rule hit also lands in the upper anomaly-model) Tj
T*
(tail. Confidence is lower for ML-only events because anomaly detection can also) Tj
T*
(surface legitimate edge cases such as unusual campaigns, regional spikes,) Tj
T*
(testing traffic, or rare but valid user behaviour.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimate is based on rule/model agreement, strength of rule evidence,) Tj
T*
(operational tier, selected anomaly class, and the known absence of labels. It) Tj
T*
(should guide review priority, not replace labelled validation or policy) Tj
T*
(approval.) Tj
