T*
( Appendix C: Model Definition) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Extended Isolation Forest is an unsupervised anomaly-detection model. It does) Tj
T*
(not learn from known bot labels. Instead, it asks which events are easier to) Tj
T*
(isolate from the rest of the batch using random feature-space splits.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In plain English, events that look very different from the main population tend) Tj
T*
(to be isolated more quickly and receive higher anomaly scores. This is useful) Tj
T*
(for an unlabelled dataset, but it also means the model detects unusual) Tj
T*
(behaviour rather than confirmed fraud. The model output is strongest when it) Tj
T*
(agrees with transparent rule evidence and weakest when it stands alone without) Tj
T*
(feature-deviation review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Methods evaluated but not selected:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Method | Why it was not preferred |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| K-means clustering | K-means is useful when compact, roughly spherical clusters are) Tj
T*
(expected. Bot-click traffic is sparse, skewed, and heavy-tailed, so forcing every event) Tj
T*
(into a cluster makes the output harder to explain and less reliable for rare anomalies.) Tj
T*
