(| Standard Isolation Forest | Standard Isolation Forest is a strong baseline, but its) Tj
T*
(axis-aligned splits can be less expressive when anomalous behaviour is a combination of) Tj
T*
(several weak signals. Extended Isolation Forest uses random hyperplane splits, which) Tj
T*
(better matches the multivariate footprint of repeated, bursty, and concentrated traffic.) Tj
T*
(|) Tj
T*
(| DBSCAN | DBSCAN can find dense groups and outliers, but it is sensitive to distance) Tj
T*
(scaling and neighbourhood parameters. With mixed count, timing, entropy, and) Tj
T*
(categorical-frequency features, it was less stable as a default production choice for) Tj
T*
(repeatable local batch runs. |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Extended Isolation Forest was preferred because it preserves the main advantage) Tj
T*
(of unsupervised Isolation Forest-style detection while giving a more flexible) Tj
T*
(view of multivariate anomalies. It also fits the operating constraints of this) Tj
T*
(project: no labels, a local batch pipeline, explainable feature engineering,) Tj
T*
(and a need to combine model scores with transparent rules.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
